
$ python -m pip install requests                #To install Requests, simply run this simple command in your terminal of choice:

$ git clone git://github.com/psf/requests.git   #Requests is actively developed on GitHub, where the code is always available.
                                                #You can either clone the public repository:

$ curl -OL https://github.com/psf/requests/tarball/main       #Or, download the tarball:
                                                              #optionally, zipball is also available (for Windows users).                                                
$ cd requests                                                 #Once you have a copy of the source, you can embed it in your own Python package, or install it into your site-packages easily:
$ python -m pip install .
